      <citeinfo>
        <title>PLSS: Survey System, BLM</title>
        <geoform>vector digital data</geoform>
        <onlink>http://gis.arkansas.gov</onlink>
      </citeinfo>
    </citation>
    <descript>
      <abstract>A Survey System is a named or numbered area of land that can be identified by a type and a designator. The survey system is generally a simultaneous conveyance that defines an area of land within which there is a consistent method of land description. The survey systems included lands that were established prior to PLSS survey and were not included in the public domain lands. Non-rectangular components of the PLSS are in the PLSS Special Surveys feature class. The first, second and third division attributes are provided if available.</abstract>
      <purpose>To provide a mapped area for the subdivisions, condominiums and other surveys that defines the external extent of surveyed areas. The divisions of survey systems are defined in this feature class and may be included. The other notable content of this feature class are areas within public domain states (PLSS States) that were established prior to PLSS Survey. These areas were never part of the public domain and are not included in the PLSS feature classes. Features such as French and Spanish claims and pre-existing land grants are in this feature class</purpose>
    </descript>
